wpt.desc: York County Sunday Drive # 18 by ghost9mm, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: York County Sunday Drive # 18
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: When we were kids, after church on Sunday my Dad would go for a Sunday drive, we would aways end up at grandma's house...gas was about 25 cents a gallon.. This series are all guardrail or sign post caches and are all keyholders. Nothing difficult here, all I ask is take the time to put things back the right way..there is parking for at least one car.. BRING A PEN

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Quick find on my way home from a business trip. The bag isn't sealing (it's torn near the seal), and the log was damp. TFTC!
